    "synopsis": "Baggit and Clodde are back on the run — a bounty on both their heads, a smuggling job spectacularly gone wrong, and Tabidiah Kruger's memory of them very much intact. Holed up in a Varangantuan reclamation yard, Baggit hears a rumour with teeth: somewhere in the bones of a wrecked Imperial voidship scheduled for breaking lies the Wraithbone Phoenix, a xenos relic worth enough to buy their lives back twice over. The catch is that everyone else in the city seems to have heard the same rumour. Alec Worley's full-length follow-up to Dredge Runners turns the ratling-and-ogryn double act into a deceptively dark caper — chases through ship-hulks, double-crosses among bounty hunters, and a friendship that keeps surviving the worst decisions the two of them can make.",
